<div class="row welcome-row">
  <center>
  <h1 class="large-header hidden"><%= @title %></h1>
  <h5 class="hidden" id="subtitle" ><%= @subtitle %></h5>
  </center>
</div>
<div class="row" id="about-me">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-3"></div>
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <center><h2>Who Am I?</h2></center>
      <div class="card" style="padding:0px;">
        <div class="card-block">
          <h4 class="card-title">
          <center><img src="https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/7366444?v=3&s=460" class="profile-image img-circle" alt="tmobaird"></center>
          </h4>
          <p class="card-text">
            <div class="show">
              <p>My name is Thomas Baird and I was born, raised, and am currently living in Alexandria, VA. I am a 23 year old software engineer for Booz Allen Hamilton with a strong passion for building software, especially with Ruby and Ruby on Rails. </p>
            </div>
          <div class="additional-content hidden">
            <p><strong>Languages</strong>: <br />
              <%= image_tag "logos/languages/ruby.png", class: "icon-image", title: "Ruby", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
              <% @logos.select { |name| name.include?("/languages/")}.each do |logo| %>
                <% if logo.split('/').last == "cpp.png" %>
                  <%= image_tag "logos/languages/#{logo.split('/').last}", class: "icon-image", title: "C++", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
                <% else %>
                  <%= image_tag "logos/languages/#{logo.split('/').last}", class: "icon-image", title: "#{logo.split('/').last.remove('.png').titleize}", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
                <% end %>
              <% end %>
            </p>
            <p><strong>Frameworks</strong>: <br />
              <%= image_tag "logos/frameworks/ruby_on_rails.png", class: "icon-image", title: "Ruby on Rails", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
              <% @logos.select { |name| name.include?("/frameworks/")}.each do |logo| %>
                <%= image_tag "logos/frameworks/#{logo.split('/').last}", class: "icon-image", title: "#{logo.split('/').last.remove('.png').titleize}", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
              <% end %>
            </p>
            <p><strong>Tools</strong>: <br />
              <%= image_tag "logos/tools/rspec.png", class: "icon-image", title: "RSpec", "data-toggle" => "tooltip" %>
              <% @logos.select { |name| name.include?("/tools/")}.each do |logo| %>
                <%= image_tag "logos/tools/#{logo.split('/').last}", class: "icon-image", title: "#{logo.split('/').last.remove('.png').titleize}", "data-toggle" => "tooltip"  %>
              <% end %>
            </p>
            <center>
              <hr />
              <a href="https://github.com/tmobaird"><%= image_tag("github.png", class: "icon-image") %></a>
              <a href="https://twitter.com/tmobaird"><%= image_tag("twitter.png", class: "icon-image") %></a>
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tmobaird"><%= image_tag("linkedin.png", class: "icon-image") %></a>
              <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCQJvNoVOHD7xsr9qa_ER5mA"><%= image_tag("youtube.png", class: "icon-image") %></a>
            </center>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-footer">
          <span class="btn btn-sm btn-link pull-right show-additional-content">Show More</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-3"></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row section-row bottom-border" id="projects">
  <center><h1 class="medium-header">Projects</h1></center>
  <!-- Need to make this render a partial for an array of project objects -->
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-block">
          <h4 class="card-title">
          <center>Guidebox Wrapper <%= image_tag("logos/languages/ruby.png", class:"project-image img-rounded") %></center>
          </h4>
          <p class="card-text">Guidebox Wrapper is a RubyGem that functions as an api wrapper for the Guidebox API. The Guidebox API is a searchable database of Movie and TV records. This gem allow you to query this API in a quick and efficient way, that requires for the least possible queries to obtain the desired information. </p>
          <center>
          <a href="#" class="icon-image"><%= image_tag("github.png", class:"icon-image") %></a>
          <a href="#" class="icon-image"><%= image_tag("cursor.png", class:"icon-image") %></a>
          </center>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-block">
          <h4 class="card-title">
          <center>Words&Moves <%= image_tag("wandm.png", class:"project-image img-rounded") %></center>
          </h4>
          <p class="card-text">Words&Moves is a Ruby on Rails application that lists all the popular events that are happening in a given area or region. On top of this it also includes posts related to these events that can serve function as guides or useful information to people that will attend these events. </p>
          <center>
          <a href="#" class="icon-image"><%= image_tag("github.png", class:"icon-image") %></a>
          <a href="#" class="icon-image"><%= image_tag("cursor.png", class:"icon-image") %></a>
          </center>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
